Source: httpd
Maintainer: Sean Mackrory <mackrorysd@apache.org>
Section: misc
Priority: optional
Standards-Version: 3.9.2
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 9), libaprutil1-dev

Package: apachecon
Architecture: any
# Architectures:
#   any: target host architecture
#   all: architecture-agnostic
#   i386 / i686: 32-bit examples
#   amd64: 64-bit example (RPMs would say x86_64 instead)
Depends: ${misc:Depends}
Description: A robust, commercial-grade, featureful, and freely-available open-source HTTP (Web) server.
 The Apache HTTP Server Project is an effort to develop and maintain an
 open-source HTTP server for modern operating systems including UNIX and
 Windows NT. The goal of this project is to provide a secure, efficient and
 extensible server that provides HTTP services in sync with the current HTTP
 standards.

Package: apachecon-dev
Architecture: any
Depends: apachecon
Description: Development headers for Apache
 The development headers for Apache
